  "story": {
    "eyebrow": "Our House",
    "title": "Four centuries of stone, refined for the way you travel <em>today</em>.",
    "paragraphs": [
      "Anchora test test test occupies a 17th-century stone house in the strict centre of Herceg Novi's old town — a building shaped by Venetian, Austro-Hungarian and Mediterranean hands, now carefully reimagined into six distinct apartments.",
      "Original walls, hand-hewn timber beams and quiet inner courtyards have been preserved alongside considered modern comforts: linen-soft beds, deep showers, fast Wi-Fi and air conditioning. Rustic in spirit, luxurious in detail."
    ],
    "signature": "— It feels like a private home, because it once was.",
